product_name: Anastasia Beverly HillsDIPBROW Waterproof, Smudge Proof Brow Pomade
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeThe Anastasia Beverly Hills DIPBROW® Pomade is a full-pigment, waterproof eyebrow pomade for creating fuller-looking, defined brows. The unique formula adheres to brow hairs, builds the appearance of fullness, and dries down to a seamless matte finish.
details: DetailsBenefitsLong-wearing, smudge-resistant, waterproof formulaCreamy texture is easy to pick up on the brush, glides on smoothly to the skin and hair, adheres without building too much, and blends out for a natural-looking finishAllows for versatility in application, giving you the artistic ability to create everything from natural-looking hairs to bold outlining and fillingHighly pigmented formula mimics hairlike texture, making it ideal for creating hair where it is sparse or adding volume to hair that already existsAlthough waterproof, the formula allows time for blending before drying to a matte finishFeaturesCruelty-freeWaterproofDermatologist testedGluten-freeOil-freeItem 2272979How To UseDipbrow is best applied with Anastasia Beverly Hills Brush 12, an angled brow brush with short, stiff bristles. You can easily outline and fill a perfect eyebrow. After applying the desired amount of color, be sure to blend with the clean spooley end of Brush 12. Never apply the pomade by directly putting your brush into the pot and applying the product on your brows. To ensure you have the perfect amount needed for application, dip your brush into the pot and swipe it across the inside of the cap - this will allow you to remove excess product, or collect more as-needed.Precautions: Discontinue use if signs of rash or irritation appear. Remove with waterproof makeup remover.IngredientsCyclopentasiloxane, Isododecane, Cyclohexasiloxane, Silica, Polyethylene, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, Ozokerite, Bis-Diglyceryl Polyacyladipate-2, Silica Dimethyl Silylate, Mica, Tocopheryl Acetate, Caprylyl Glycol, Ethylhexylglycerin, Propylparaben. May Contain: Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499), Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Bismuth Oxychloride (CI 77163).Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Dipbrow is best applied with Anastasia Beverly Hills Brush 12, an angled brow brush with short, stiff bristles. You can easily outline and fill a perfect eyebrow. After applying the desired amount of color, be sure to blend with the clean spooley end of Brush 12. Never apply the pomade by directly putting your brush into the pot and applying the product on your brows. To ensure you have the perfect amount needed for application, dip your brush into the pot and swipe it across the inside of the cap - this will allow you to remove excess product, or collect more as-needed.Precautions: Discontinue use if signs of rash or irritation appear. Remove with waterproof makeup remover.

reviews.headline: 2016 brows are back
reviews.comments: So far this has been my go-to brow product and it helps me get my brows done so much faster. I would say this is more for people who have been doing their brows for much longer than beginners. I love how easy it is to work with and shape my brows!

reviews.headline: Been using for almost a decade now
reviews.comments: I've tried other brow products but I always go back to my this one. Easy to use, lasts for months and doesn't budge but easy to remove if you overdo it. I use the Anastasia brow brush to create natural strokes. People have told me that they can't tell I use a brow products so it must look very natural. Doesn't lift if you add the brow gel over the top. Please don't discontinue!

reviews.headline: I actually thought it was going to be a little lighter than
reviews.comments: Overall, I like the smoothness of it. I like that it is water resistant it doesn't smear much but I was thinking because it's Auburn and my hair color is Auburn. It would match exactly and unfortunately it does not yet still I am satisfied.

reviews.headline: Love it!
reviews.comments: I've used this product in the past and I absolutely loved it. It's easy to use. If I messed up while applying I would use a q-tip and toner to either remove it all or define my brows how I wanted. I slept in this and it would stay put! 100% recommend!

reviews.headline: Worth every penny
reviews.comments: I have oily skin and work long hours, so I need a brow product that doesn't budge. I've bought L'Oreal's Unbelievabrow for years, but this pomade is WAY better for less than $10 more. The color is beautiful and it doesn't smudge. Highly recommend!

reviews.headline: Eyebrows all day and night!
reviews.comments: My best friend did my makeup for my wedding, one she used this product on me and ever since then I knew I had to have it! Taught myself the right way to do my eyebrows, and I love this product and it will last me forever! Won't be switching it up or going back to my old eyebrows ways!

reviews.headline: Works with Stamps/Stencils!
reviews.comments: I had been using the Trio pomade, but it dries out too quickly.  This pomade works VERY well with a sponge and stencil. I am a dark ash blonde and bought the taupe. Buildable, natural, creamy, not chalky. VERY pleased!

reviews.headline: Last long and make my lash look full.
reviews.comments: Love this dipbrow it Last long on my face and it makes my lash full.

reviews.headline: This is a life saver!
reviews.comments: Anastasia's Dipbrow pomade has been my miracle product.  I went from using those  retractable eyebrow pencils from the drug store to this and omg what a difference.   I got sick of constantly spending money on those pencils that always break,  are difficult to apply,  and just don't have a good amount of pigment in them.   Problem solved with this product!  This stuff is highly pigmented and I can already tell it's going to last me a very long time.   A little bit goes a very long way.  I apply it with an Anastasia angled brush and it literally stays on all day.   No smudging or fading.   I love this product and I highly recommend it... especially if you are tired of constantly buying those eyebrow pencils that always break.
